# Obsidian vault I/O (local Windows)

**Brain:** `D:\Obsidian\Obsidian\00_Brain`  
**Project vaults:** `D:\Obsidian\Obsidian\40_VSCode\<Project>\`

## Mandatory tool choice

| Action | Tool | Do not use |
|--------|------|------------|
| Read / search vault | Native `Read` / `Grep` on `D:\Obsidian\...` | MCP `obsidian-*` for reads |
| Write / edit vault | Native `Write` / `StrReplace` on `D:\Obsidian\...` | MCP in Agent mode |
| Repo code | Native workspace tools | — |

`obsidian-brain` MCP points at the same `D:\` files — it adds latency and UI noise, not capability.

## MCP fallback (writes only)

Use Obsidian MCP for vault writes **only when**:

1. **Ask mode** blocks native Write/StrReplace, or
2. Native Write **fails** (path/permission), or
3. User **explicitly** requests MCP

If MCP is used, footer Memory must note: `vault ✓ path (MCP fallback — <reason>)`.

## Other MCP

Context7, Serena, Shopify, etc. per repo `docs/TOKEN-STACK.md` — not for vault file I/O.

**One tool per vault file per turn.** Never Read a file via MCP if you already read it natively this turn.
